==English==

===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
From Greek [[πέτρος]] ''(petros,'' [[stone]]) + [[ἰχώρ]] ''(ichor,'' [[ichor]]), thus ‘rock-essence.’ The term was coined by two Australian researchers in 1964 for an article in the journal Nature. 

===Noun===
'''petrichor'''
#The [[scent]] of [[rain]] on [[dry]] [[earth]]. 
#The yellow [[organic]] [[oil]] that yields this scent.